Kent Richard JONES, Appellant, v. John STUART, Appellee. No. 05-3613. United States Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. Submitted: Dec. 7, 2006. Filed: Dec. 14, 2006. John Remington Graham, St-Agapit Comte de Lotbiniere 180 Haut de la Par*505oisse Quebec Canada GOS LZO, Kent Richard Jones, c/o John Remington Graham St-Agapit Comte de Lotbiniere, argued, Quebec Canada GOS LZO, for Appellant. John Steven Garry, Attorney General’s Office, argued, St. Paul, MN, for Appellee. Before SMITH, MAGILL and BENTON, Circuit Judges.

[UNPUBLISHED]

PER CURIAM.

Kent Richard Jones appeals the district court’s1 dismissal with prejudice of his 42 U.S.C. § 1988 complaint. Having carefully reviewed the record, we conclude dismissal of the complaint was proper for the reasons explained by the district court. Accordingly, we affirm the judgment. See 8th Cir. R. 47B.

. The Honorable Joan N. Ericksen, United States District Judge for the District of Minnesota, adopting the report and recommendations of the Honorable Jonathan G. Lebedoff, United States Magistrate Judge for the District of Minnesota, now retired.
